WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:44.359 --> 00:01:47.404
<i>Target in position.
All hands back to stations.</i>

3
00:02:00.626 --> 00:02:01.835
<i>Prepare to fire.</i>

4
00:02:14.931 --> 00:02:18.310
Please!
Get me out of here!

5
00:04:39.743 --> 00:04:42.287
<i>Ceres was once covered in ice.</i>

6
00:04:43.997 --> 00:04:47.708
<i>Enough water
for 1.000 generations.</i>

7
00:04:47.709 --> 00:04:51.338
<i>Until Earth and Mars stripped
it away for themselves.</i>

8
00:04:54.216 --> 00:04:58.594
<i>This station became the most
vital port in the Belt.</i>

9
00:04:58.595 --> 00:05:02.515
<i>But. the immense wealth
and resources that flow
through our gates</i>

10
00:05:02.516 --> 00:05:04.934
<i>were never meant for us.</i>

11
00:05:04.935 --> 00:05:07.186
<i>Belters work the docks.</i>

12
00:05:07.187 --> 00:05:10.856
<i>loading and unloading
precious cargo.</i>

13
00:05:10.857 --> 00:05:14.069
<i>We fix the pipes and filters
that keep this rock
living and breathing.</i>

14
00:05:16.822 --> 00:05:21.283
<i>We Belters toil and suffer.
without hope and without end.</i>

15
00:05:21.284 --> 00:05:24.620
<i>And for what?</i>

16
00:05:24.621 --> 00:05:28.707
<i>One day. Mars will use
its might to wrest control
of Ceres from Earth.</i>

17
00:05:28.708 --> 00:05:31.627
<i>and Earth will go to war
to take it back.</i>

18
00:05:31.628 --> 00:05:34.255
<i>It’s all the same to us.</i>

19
00:05:34.256 --> 00:05:37.842
<i>No matter who controls
Ceres. our home.</i>

20
00:05:37.843 --> 00:05:41.762
<i>to them. we will
always be slaves.</i>

21
00:05:41.763 --> 00:05:44.765
<i>That’s all we are
to the Earthers and Dusters.</i>

22
00:05:44.766 --> 00:05:48.644
<i>They built their solar system
on our backs.</i>

23
00:05:48.645 --> 00:05:51.313
<i>spilled the blood
of a million of our brothers.</i>

24
00:05:51.314 --> 00:05:55.359
<i>But in their eyes.
we’re not even human anymore.</i>

25
00:05:55.360 --> 00:05:57.520
<i>So. the next time you look
in the mirror. say the word.</i>

26
00:05:58.029 --> 00:05:59.405
<i>Slave.</i>

27
00:05:59.406 --> 00:06:01.740
<i>Every time we
demand to be heard.</i>

28
00:06:01.741 --> 00:06:04.743
<i>they hold back our water.
owkwa beltalowda.</i>

29
00:06:04.744 --> 00:06:07.121
<i>ration our air.
ereluf beltalowda.</i>

30
00:06:07.122 --> 00:06:09.164
<i>until we crawl back
into our holes.</i>

31
00:06:09.165 --> 00:06:11.501
imbobo beltalowda.
<i>and do as we are told.</i>

32
00:06:14.546 --> 00:06:16.922
Watch your eyes.

33
00:06:16.923 --> 00:06:19.258
People get killed over
a wrong look around here.

34
00:06:19.259 --> 00:06:20.801
We could run him
in for inciting.

35
00:06:20.802 --> 00:06:23.221
Time and a place.
<i>Hey. you. Badge.</i>

36
00:06:25.974 --> 00:06:28.225
<i>Day’s coming soon. keya?</i>

37
00:06:28.226 --> 00:06:30.144
<i>And when the blood
is on the wall.</i>

38
00:06:30.145 --> 00:06:31.438
sasa ke <i>which side you’re on?</i>

39
00:06:33.231 --> 00:06:34.648
Yeah. I’ll know.

40
00:06:34.649 --> 00:06:36.526
<i>See you then.</i> welwala.

41
00:06:38.028 --> 00:06:40.405
What is <i>welwala?</i>

42
00:06:43.074 --> 00:06:44.242
“Traitor to my people.”

43
00:06:46.369 --> 00:06:47.489
Come on. we have work to do.

44
00:06:56.713 --> 00:06:58.673
Just tell me what
happened. Take your time.

45
00:07:13.939 --> 00:07:15.539
Forgotten arm. <i>keya?</i>
Forgotten arm. yeah.

46
00:07:27.369 --> 00:07:30.413
If any of these guys
come round again. <i>shoah.</i>

47
00:07:36.962 --> 00:07:38.922
All right.
let in the coroner.
Let him clean it up.

48
00:07:47.097 --> 00:07:49.515
What did she mean.
“forgotten arm”?

49
00:07:49.516 --> 00:07:51.809
The thing you never see coming.

50
00:07:51.810 --> 00:07:56.605
Don’t start. You are never
gonna pass for a Belter.

51
00:07:56.606 --> 00:07:58.732
Every time they look
at you. they’re always
gonna see Earth.

52
00:07:58.733 --> 00:08:01.610
Coming from a guy
dressed like an Earther.

53
00:08:01.611 --> 00:08:02.771
What’s the deal with the hat?

54
00:08:04.531 --> 00:08:05.740
Keeps the rain off my head.

55
00:08:13.707 --> 00:08:15.000
Okay. What am I
looking for?

56
00:08:15.792 --> 00:08:18.168
All right.

57
00:08:18.169 --> 00:08:20.879
See that piss-poor
rock hopper down there?

58
00:08:20.880 --> 00:08:23.090
He’s trying to cover it up
with that baggy flight suit.

59
00:08:23.091 --> 00:08:25.759
See the way the skin
hangs off his bones?

60
00:08:25.760 --> 00:08:28.220
You get the red eyes
and the shakes

61
00:08:28.221 --> 00:08:31.223
when your body rejects
the growth hormones.

62
00:08:31.224 --> 00:08:33.308
You also get that from
a little too much whiskey.

63
00:08:33.309 --> 00:08:35.519
Nah. tremors. man.

64
00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.813
That’s from growing up in low-G.

65
00:08:37.814 --> 00:08:40.357
Your muscles don’t
develop right.

66
00:08:40.358 --> 00:08:43.986
I guess that’s from
generations in low-G. huh?

67
00:08:43.987 --> 00:08:46.531
Someday. I’d say
every Belter’s gonna
look just like that.

68
00:08:49.576 --> 00:08:51.201
What about you?

69
00:08:51.202 --> 00:08:52.453
What about me?

70
00:08:52.454 --> 00:08:54.329
What’s your tell?

71
00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:56.373
Let me help you
with that. <i>inyaloda.</i>

72
00:08:56.374 --> 00:08:59.752
This one. he has spurs
at the top of his spine

73
00:08:59.753 --> 00:09:01.962
where the bones
didn’t fuse right.

74
00:09:01.963 --> 00:09:04.465
He got the cheap
bone density juice
when he was a child.

75
00:09:04.466 --> 00:09:07.384
Probably a ward of the station.

76
00:09:07.385 --> 00:09:10.679
So. even if
he disguises himself.
he’s just like me.

77
00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:13.849
I am nothing like you. longbone.

78
00:09:13.850 --> 00:09:17.227
Take your OPA bullshit
back to the Medina.

79
00:09:17.228 --> 00:09:18.812
and wait for the revolution

80
00:09:18.813 --> 00:09:20.647
with all the rest of the
victims.

81
00:09:20.648 --> 00:09:22.400
Please. why don’t
you go outside…

82
00:09:23.860 --> 00:09:25.111
Lunch break’s over.

83
00:09:43.338 --> 00:09:44.922
Hey. <i>voyu…</i>

84
00:09:44.923 --> 00:09:47.132
Detective.

85
00:09:47.133 --> 00:09:48.759
I’ve been looking
all over for you.

86
00:09:48.760 --> 00:09:51.386
Hmm. I trust you changed
those air filters. right?

87
00:09:51.387 --> 00:09:53.472
Full compliance. <i>mi Sa-sa.</i>

88
00:09:53.473 --> 00:09:54.473
Good. good.

89
00:09:56.559 --> 00:09:58.519
<i>Now arriving.</i>

90
00:09:58.520 --> 00:10:00.896
<i>Mid-town level…
No need to
pay a visit. then.</i>

91
00:10:00.897 --> 00:10:03.257
<i>Exit for Star Helix Police
and Emergency Services.
Excuse me.</i>

92
00:10:03.733 --> 00:10:05.527
Come on.

93
00:10:15.745 --> 00:10:17.871
<i>Okay. I’m gonna
ask you one more time.</i>

94
00:10:17.872 --> 00:10:20.582
Stop grinning like an idiot
and give me your real name.

95
00:10:20.583 --> 00:10:22.501
I promise you things
will not go well for you
if you do not…

96
00:10:22.502 --> 00:10:23.752
Jesus. Miller!
Do you hear her?

97
00:10:23.753 --> 00:10:25.838
Miller! Hey!

98
00:10:25.839 --> 00:10:27.714
Get the cuffs off.
If I want his ass kicked.
I’ll do it myself.

99
00:10:27.715 --> 00:10:29.967
I know who you are!
I’ll find you!

100
00:10:29.968 --> 00:10:31.927
I’ll find you!
I’ll find you!

101
00:10:31.928 --> 00:10:33.929
Any laws against
beating up suspects?

102
00:10:33.930 --> 00:10:35.765
No laws in Ceres.
Just cops.

103
00:10:39.978 --> 00:10:41.812
I have something for you.

104
00:10:41.813 --> 00:10:44.189
New contract.

105
00:10:44.190 --> 00:10:46.442
Just you. Not Havelock.
He’s too new.

106
00:10:47.861 --> 00:10:49.862
You sidelining me. Captain?

107
00:10:49.863 --> 00:10:52.489
No. this is off-book.
On your own time.

108
00:10:52.490 --> 00:10:54.658
A favor someone down on Earth
is doing for a shareholder.

109
00:10:54.659 --> 00:10:56.618
Oh. we’re groveling to
the shareholders now?

110
00:10:56.619 --> 00:10:57.619
I need someone discreet.

111
00:10:57.620 --> 00:10:58.746
Ah. Say no more.

112
00:10:59.914 --> 00:11:02.749
I’ve linked you into the files.

113
00:11:02.750 --> 00:11:05.961
A little lost daughter case.
Ariadne and Jules-Pierre Mao.

114
00:11:05.962 --> 00:11:07.421
Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile?

115
00:11:07.422 --> 00:11:09.256
They’re Luna-based.

116
00:11:09.257 --> 00:11:11.133
They do a lot of
shipping through here.

117
00:11:11.134 --> 00:11:13.428
And they misplaced a daughter?

118
00:11:16.097 --> 00:11:18.682
Black sheep. Went to college.
got involved with a group

119
00:11:18.683 --> 00:11:20.726
called the “Far Horizons
Foundation.”

120
00:11:20.727 --> 00:11:22.520
Students. With big ideas
and big mouths.

121
00:11:25.356 --> 00:11:27.733
Why do the parents want her
found all of a sudden?

122
00:11:27.734 --> 00:11:29.818
Probably got tired of her
embarrassing the old man.

123
00:11:29.819 --> 00:11:30.945
It’s all in the files.

124
00:11:37.118 --> 00:11:39.953
So… So. what’s
my contract exactly?

125
00:11:39.954 --> 00:11:42.873
Find Julie Mao.
if she’s still here on Ceres.
detain her. and ship her home.

126
00:11:42.874 --> 00:11:44.918
Kidnap job.
My pleasure.

127
00:11:55.970 --> 00:11:59.014
So. what you gonna do
with your bonus check
when we get this ice to Ceres?

128
00:11:59.015 --> 00:12:01.516
Well. I’m not gonna make
the same mistake as last time.

129
00:12:01.517 --> 00:12:02.809
Casino before brothel.

130
00:12:02.810 --> 00:12:04.686
You got cleaned out.

131
00:12:04.687 --> 00:12:06.647
Yeah. And let me tell you.

132
00:12:06.648 --> 00:12:09.608
brothels on Ceres
don’t like extending credit.

133
00:12:09.609 --> 00:12:11.985
Bet I can load twice the ice
that you do in half the time.

134
00:12:11.986 --> 00:12:14.238
Am I smelling a wager. <i>ke?</i>

135
00:12:14.239 --> 00:12:16.907
Not yet.
But I will drag my…

136
00:12:16.908 --> 00:12:17.908
Watch out!

137
00:12:46.062 --> 00:12:48.188
You’re entirely
too good at this.

138
00:12:48.189 --> 00:12:50.482
I told you. I’ve got
no power to get you
promoted on this ship.

139
00:12:50.483 --> 00:12:52.484
Well. then I take it back.

140
00:12:52.485 --> 00:12:53.986
<i>Standby for thrust correction.</i>

141
00:12:53.987 --> 00:12:55.655
<i>Warning. Gravity has…</i>

142
00:13:00.660 --> 00:13:01.980
<i>Holden. report to
the flight deck.</i>

143
00:13:04.872 --> 00:13:05.999
We never saw it.

144
00:13:07.375 --> 00:13:10.836
Sorry. cowboy. but we did.

145
00:13:10.837 --> 00:13:13.171
<i>We got a code 22. Cameron Paj.
Can’t find the XO.</i>

146
00:13:13.172 --> 00:13:14.772
All right. all right.
I’ll hunt him down.

147
00:13:15.466 --> 00:13:16.551
Don’t get dressed.

148
00:13:19.012 --> 00:13:20.929
Hey. Paj. how’s the arm?

149
00:13:20.930 --> 00:13:23.807
Looking good.
Still got a few
nerves. though.

150
00:13:23.808 --> 00:13:25.434
Shed’s been telling me
how the prosthetic’s
gonna hook up.

151
00:13:25.435 --> 00:13:26.852
Well. you know that
naturally. the company’ll try

152
00:13:26.853 --> 00:13:29.104
to screw you out of
a good one. right?

153
00:13:29.105 --> 00:13:31.773
I’ve been signed on
long enough to get one
with force feedback.

154
00:13:31.774 --> 00:13:34.359
pressure and temp sensors.
the whole package.

155
00:13:34.360 --> 00:13:36.111
I know.
What you should have
is that new bio-gel

156
00:13:36.112 --> 00:13:37.529
they developed
on the inner planets.

157
00:13:37.530 --> 00:13:38.572
Then you wouldn’t need
a prosthetic.

158
00:13:38.573 --> 00:13:40.157
It regrows the limb perfectly.

159
00:13:40.158 --> 00:13:42.409
Screw the Inners
and their magic Jell-O.

160
00:13:42.410 --> 00:13:44.453
No offense. Holden.

161
00:13:44.454 --> 00:13:46.330
No. I’d rather
a Belter-built fake
any day.

162
00:13:46.331 --> 00:13:47.581
That’s ’cause you’re
stubborn as hell.

163
00:13:47.582 --> 00:13:49.082
No worries. Paj.

164
00:13:49.083 --> 00:13:51.043
Hey. I need some Z-PRO.

165
00:13:51.044 --> 00:13:52.836
Been cleaned out for two weeks.

166
00:13:52.837 --> 00:13:54.671
You’re gonna have to
count sheep. sorry.

167
00:13:54.672 --> 00:13:57.799
Oh. I do have something
a little stronger. though.

168
00:13:57.800 --> 00:13:59.635
if you’ve got the. uh. scrip.

169
00:14:02.597 --> 00:14:04.931
Hey. seriously. Holden.

170
00:14:04.932 --> 00:14:07.225
You won’t let them screw me
out of an arm. will you?
I don’t wanna used one.

171
00:14:07.226 --> 00:14:08.746
I’m just a clock-puncher
like you. Paj.

172
00:14:10.146 --> 00:14:12.022
Hey! Hey. you seen
the XO?

173
00:14:12.023 --> 00:14:13.774
No. <i>sa-sa.</i>

174
00:14:13.775 --> 00:14:15.067
Just follow the reek of whiskey.

175
00:14:15.068 --> 00:14:16.361
That’s not nice.
It’s the truth.

176
00:14:17.862 --> 00:14:19.905
You didn’t sign the PRP.

177
00:14:19.906 --> 00:14:22.115
I didn’t sign the what?

178
00:14:22.116 --> 00:14:23.743
It’s the retrofit…

179
00:14:27.372 --> 00:14:30.999
It’s the retrofit proposal
to overhaul this bucket
before it breaks apart.

180
00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:33.168
Ah.
If Naomi says
it’ll happen.

181
00:14:33.169 --> 00:14:34.836
you can take it to the bank.

182
00:14:34.837 --> 00:14:36.963
Listen. kids.
I’ve been here
longer than you.

183
00:14:36.964 --> 00:14:39.132
It’s way cheaper for
the company to settle up
with a few widows

184
00:14:39.133 --> 00:14:41.134
than to overhaul this old barge.

185
00:14:41.135 --> 00:14:43.720
The truth.

186
00:14:43.721 --> 00:14:47.475
Besides. the <i>Cant</i> is
a legend for her scars.
Badges of endurance.

187
00:14:49.143 --> 00:14:50.223
Hey. do you have a pry bar?

188
00:14:52.730 --> 00:14:53.815
Make sure I get it back.

189
00:14:56.442 --> 00:15:00.904
You must tell me the amazing
story of how you managed to
become a second officer.

190
00:15:00.905 --> 00:15:02.745
- My biggest failure in life.
- Look out below!

191
00:15:03.866 --> 00:15:06.076
Welcome to the rodeo.

192
00:15:06.077 --> 00:15:08.537
Ladies and gentlemen.
please sit back.
relax and enjoy the ride.

193
00:15:08.538 --> 00:15:11.123
Ceres Station. here we come.

194
00:15:11.124 --> 00:15:12.916
Please adjust your
tray tables and seat backs

195
00:15:12.917 --> 00:15:14.876
into their upright
and locked positions…

196
00:15:14.877 --> 00:15:16.002
Shut up and fly. would ya?

197
00:15:16.003 --> 00:15:17.421
You. too. Boo Boo.

198
00:15:17.422 --> 00:15:19.048
Okay.
reverse thrust. BS…

199
00:15:20.925 --> 00:15:22.217
How are we looking. kids?

200
00:15:22.218 --> 00:15:24.261
It’s easy as
picklin’ eggs. Hoss.

201
00:15:24.262 --> 00:15:26.304
Paj needs
approval for a new arm.

202
00:15:26.305 --> 00:15:28.640
I gotta get XO on it.
Have you seen him?

203
00:15:28.641 --> 00:15:29.892
If I said I had. I’d be lyin’.

204
00:15:34.772 --> 00:15:35.898
Hey. XO!

205
00:15:43.448 --> 00:15:44.823
All right. I’m coming in.

206
00:15:44.824 --> 00:15:46.264
and I don’t wanna see
anything hairy.

207
00:15:59.255 --> 00:16:00.590
<i>Daffodil</i>

208
00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:04.802
<i>A daffodil</i>

209
00:16:09.098 --> 00:16:11.726
Rosa…
Priscitha…

210
00:16:13.186 --> 00:16:14.312
Roses.

211
00:16:17.690 --> 00:16:19.024
Daisies.

212
00:16:19.025 --> 00:16:22.028
<i>Daisy</i>

213
00:16:23.905 --> 00:16:26.324
Ah. Jimmy boy.

214
00:16:29.911 --> 00:16:31.412
You know what I just
can’t figure out?

215
00:16:34.624 --> 00:16:35.624
We make it all this way.

216
00:16:37.710 --> 00:16:39.170
so far out into the darkness.

217
00:16:44.759 --> 00:16:46.319
Why couldn’t we have
brought more light?

218
00:16:51.432 --> 00:16:53.684
I hear ya…
Okay. come on. now. X.

219
00:17:01.651 --> 00:17:02.693
Oh. my God.

220
00:17:11.744 --> 00:17:13.828
<i>Just lay back. real slow. okay?</i>

221
00:17:13.829 --> 00:17:16.373
<i>What’s that?</i>

222
00:17:16.374 --> 00:17:17.666
<i>Okay. everything’s
gonna be fine. all right?</i>

223
00:17:17.667 --> 00:17:20.877
<i>Daisy. bluebell…</i>

224
00:17:20.878 --> 00:17:23.129
<i>Pull that tight.</i>

225
00:17:23.130 --> 00:17:25.632
He started
talking to his plants
about six months ago.

226
00:17:25.633 --> 00:17:27.300
I figured he would’ve
pulled himself out of it.

227
00:17:27.301 --> 00:17:28.301
So it goes.

228
00:17:31.013 --> 00:17:32.931
McDOWELL: It’s been
a long time comin’.

229
00:17:32.932 --> 00:17:35.517
Are you kidding?

230
00:17:35.518 --> 00:17:36.851
No.
I thought I was getting
my walking papers.

231
00:17:36.852 --> 00:17:38.562
What for?

232
00:17:38.563 --> 00:17:40.603
Well. fraternizing with
our navigator. for starters.

233
00:17:40.648 --> 00:17:42.357
What?

234
00:17:42.358 --> 00:17:45.944
Look. people like you.

235
00:17:45.945 --> 00:17:47.320
You get things done.
and you’re gonna make
a good XO.

236
00:17:47.321 --> 00:17:49.072
You got me
pegged wrong. Captain.

237
00:17:49.073 --> 00:17:52.409
Captain’s never wrong.
First lesson. free.

238
00:17:52.410 --> 00:17:55.620
You’ve been on the <i>Cant</i>
five years now.
Turned down two transfers.

239
00:17:55.621 --> 00:17:58.039
Face it. this is your home.
It’s your family.

240
00:17:58.040 --> 00:17:59.457
Is this where we hug?

241
00:17:59.458 --> 00:18:01.251
So. why haven’t you
moved on. then?

242
00:18:01.252 --> 00:18:03.128
Because no one tried to
push an XO badge on me.

243
00:18:03.129 --> 00:18:04.504
I like things the way they are.

244
00:18:04.505 --> 00:18:06.381
Evolve or die.

245
00:18:06.382 --> 00:18:08.008
Then at least I’ll die grinning.

246
00:18:08.009 --> 00:18:11.177
Don’t be stupid.
One of these days.

247
00:18:11.178 --> 00:18:13.054
Earth and Mars are gonna
bury the hatchet and
hammer out a treaty.

248
00:18:13.055 --> 00:18:15.265
Yeah. and now
you’re dreamin’. Cap.

249
00:18:15.266 --> 00:18:17.100
McDOWELL: I’m a man
of great vision.
You’ll see.

250
00:18:17.101 --> 00:18:19.102
Means we’ll finally get out
of the ice-hauling business

251
00:18:19.103 --> 00:18:21.021
and into the
Earth-Mars business.

252
00:18:21.022 --> 00:18:22.273
Less risk. way better reward.

253
00:18:24.066 --> 00:18:26.109
Maybe a chance
to see Earth again.

254
00:18:26.110 --> 00:18:28.194
What makes you think
I wanna see Earth again?

255
00:18:28.195 --> 00:18:30.071
You a “wanted man”
back in Montana?

256
00:18:30.072 --> 00:18:31.364
Maybe I am.

257
00:18:31.365 --> 00:18:33.658
Someday you’ll
tell me that story.

258
00:18:33.659 --> 00:18:35.536
Right after you tell me
the story about those.

259
00:18:37.330 --> 00:18:39.415
Well. those are. uh. mine.

260
00:18:40.708 --> 00:18:41.834
It’s just… There’s…

261
00:18:43.502 --> 00:18:45.128
I don’t care about your past.

262
00:18:45.129 --> 00:18:46.921
Everybody on the <i>Cant</i> is
hiding from something.

263
00:18:46.922 --> 00:18:49.424
Yeah. I appreciate
the offer. Cap.

264
00:18:49.425 --> 00:18:53.303
<i>Hey. boss. we need you
out here. You gotta see this.</i>

265
00:18:53.304 --> 00:18:54.804
McDOWELL: Hang on to this
for a couple of days.

266
00:18:54.805 --> 00:18:56.085
It might feel good
in the pocket.

267
00:19:03.356 --> 00:19:05.690
Picked up a Mayday.

268
00:19:05.691 --> 00:19:08.276
Looks like a light freighter.
Calls itself the <i>Scopuli.</i>

269
00:19:08.277 --> 00:19:10.195
Anyone else in the vicinity?

270
00:19:10.196 --> 00:19:12.947
No siree. Bob. we are the only
ship in three million clicks.

271
00:19:12.948 --> 00:19:14.658
- Of course we are.
- Got it.

272
00:19:14.659 --> 00:19:18.203
Next to a charted.
non-Belt asteroid.

273
00:19:18.204 --> 00:19:20.580
What the hell were they
doing way out there?

274
00:19:20.581 --> 00:19:22.499
We’re obligated to check it out.

275
00:19:22.500 --> 00:19:24.180
I’m well aware of the
statute. Ms. Nygaard.

276
00:19:31.050 --> 00:19:32.801
It’s pirate bait.

277
00:19:32.802 --> 00:19:35.303
That far outside
the shipping lanes?

278
00:19:35.304 --> 00:19:37.640
It’s not far out
of our way. Captain.
Two days at most.

279
00:19:41.519 --> 00:19:43.119
A delay means we lose
our berth at Ceres.

280
00:19:46.023 --> 00:19:47.274
Kiss our on-time bonus goodbye.

281
00:19:49.568 --> 00:19:51.768
I say we move on
and let the good god
Darwin sort it out.

282
00:19:55.324 --> 00:19:57.534
What goes around comes around.

283
00:19:57.535 --> 00:19:59.655
One of these days.
it’s gonna be us
stranded out there.

284
00:20:03.457 --> 00:20:06.751
Captain gave an order. people.

285
00:20:06.752 --> 00:20:08.512
Purge the logs.
We never received
that signal.

286
00:20:10.506 --> 00:20:12.091
McDOWELL: Set the watch
and proceed.

287
00:20:17.972 --> 00:20:20.598
See. you’re a natural.

288
00:20:20.599 --> 00:20:23.226
That was some real
XO shit in there.

289
00:20:23.227 --> 00:20:25.938
No. That was me
wanting to get to Ceres
worse than you.

290
00:20:43.706 --> 00:20:46.416
<i>Thanks for backing me up
on that distress call.</i>

291
00:20:46.417 --> 00:20:49.210
McDowell’s got
a nose for trouble.

292
00:20:49.211 --> 00:20:51.713
He’s been doing this
a while longer than we have.

293
00:20:51.714 --> 00:20:53.754
I guess you really are
sucking up for that XO badge.

294
00:20:54.091 --> 00:20:55.383
Turned him down flat.

295
00:20:55.384 --> 00:20:57.969
You kidding me?

296
00:20:57.970 --> 00:20:59.387
You’d be on the
short path to Captain.

297
00:20:59.388 --> 00:21:02.432
Exactly.

298
00:21:02.433 --> 00:21:05.060
Besides. if I took it.
we’d have to stop
seeing each other.

299
00:21:07.104 --> 00:21:09.314
Well. You know.

300
00:21:09.315 --> 00:21:11.484
There’s that saying about
all good things.

301
00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:18.365
I told you.
A couple more rotations
and I’d be moving on.

302
00:21:19.408 --> 00:21:22.160
A couple is…

303
00:21:22.161 --> 00:21:24.914
You know. two at least.
I assumed.

304
00:21:27.666 --> 00:21:29.417
There’s right now
and there’s later.

305
00:21:29.418 --> 00:21:31.127
Why worry about later. right?

306
00:21:31.128 --> 00:21:32.213
Right.

307
00:21:34.256 --> 00:21:35.256
Come on. Jim.
Lie down.

308
00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:40.346
I promise I won’t
lay a finger on you.

309
00:21:52.566 --> 00:21:53.776
I can’t sleep.
I’ll take over.

310
00:21:55.986 --> 00:21:57.570
I’ll buy you a bottle on Ceres.

311
00:21:57.571 --> 00:21:59.406
I’ll settle for
a good cup of coffee.

312
00:23:09.768 --> 00:23:12.687
<i>Please help me.</i>

313
00:23:12.688 --> 00:23:13.688
<i>Is anybody there? Please.</i>

314
00:23:28.203 --> 00:23:29.622
<i>Please help me.</i>

315
00:23:57.024 --> 00:23:58.608
How many times have I told you?

316
00:23:58.609 --> 00:24:00.694
This calls for tickling!

317
00:24:07.534 --> 00:24:09.827
He’ll wet himself
if you’re not careful.

318
00:24:09.828 --> 00:24:12.372
That’s
the advantage of
being a grandparent.

319
00:24:12.373 --> 00:24:14.416
I get to hand him
off to his mother.

320
00:24:23.133 --> 00:24:25.593
<i>Amma. do you have to go?</i>

321
00:24:25.594 --> 00:24:28.346
Yes. I do. I’m sorry.

322
00:24:28.347 --> 00:24:29.764
There’s someone
I need to talk to.

323
00:24:29.765 --> 00:24:31.516
Are people fighting again?

324
00:24:31.517 --> 00:24:32.685
Not yet.

325
00:24:35.062 --> 00:24:36.939
<i>That’s why we need to talk.
and tell the truth.</i>

326
00:24:41.151 --> 00:24:43.236
<i>When people don’t
tell the truth.</i>

327
00:24:43.237 --> 00:24:44.363
<i>it always ends badly.</i>

328
00:25:02.673 --> 00:25:04.609
You’ve been
linked to a radical faction
of the OPA.

329
00:25:04.633 --> 00:25:05.884
Were you just a courier?

330
00:25:09.722 --> 00:25:11.222
How long has he
been out of the tank?

331
00:25:11.223 --> 00:25:12.808
Ten hours.

332
00:25:19.356 --> 00:25:22.567
I’m sorry the gravity
of a real planet hurts.

333
00:25:22.568 --> 00:25:23.568
But it’s appropriate.

334
00:25:24.611 --> 00:25:27.572
You wish to hurt Earth.

335
00:25:27.573 --> 00:25:31.576
The Earth that is now
crushing your weak
Belter lungs.

336
00:25:31.577 --> 00:25:33.162
and your fragile Belter bones.

337
00:25:35.539 --> 00:25:37.499
All you have to do to
make it stop is talk.

338
00:25:39.710 --> 00:25:42.253
You’re an OPA terrorist.

339
00:25:42.254 --> 00:25:44.134
You were carrying contraband
stealth technology.

340
00:25:45.382 --> 00:25:46.425
What was it for?

341
00:25:51.388 --> 00:25:53.849
A whisper
will do. if that’s all
you can manage.

342
00:26:02.775 --> 00:26:03.942
Give him another 10 hours.

343
00:26:06.487 --> 00:26:07.487
If he survives. call me.

344
00:26:19.875 --> 00:26:22.419
<i>Now arriving. Medina
Exchange District.</i>

345
00:26:27.591 --> 00:26:29.258
- Everybody calm down. all right!
- Back away.

346
00:26:29.259 --> 00:26:31.428
Back up. people!

347
00:26:41.855 --> 00:26:43.649
Hey! Back up.
buddy. I’m talking to you!

348
00:26:44.733 --> 00:26:46.234
What’s up. doll?

349
00:26:46.235 --> 00:26:47.568
Cheap-ass air filters
crapped out.

350
00:26:47.569 --> 00:26:49.488
Second time this month.

351
00:26:52.157 --> 00:26:55.743
I guess
this guy pays well
to be taken care of. huh?

352
00:26:55.744 --> 00:26:58.913
Yeah. he pays our bosses
pretty well. too. pal.

353
00:26:58.914 --> 00:27:01.457
Look. don’t try to
save the whole station
on your first day.

354
00:27:01.458 --> 00:27:02.458
Pace yourself.

355
00:27:06.463 --> 00:27:07.548
Any rain yet?

356
00:27:11.385 --> 00:27:12.825
That distress call
we never received.

357
00:27:13.762 --> 00:27:16.973
it was logged with HQ.

358
00:27:16.974 --> 00:27:19.725
By some anonymous.
piece-o’-shit do-gooder
aboard this ship.

359
00:27:19.726 --> 00:27:20.768
Well. at least
somebody has a soul.

360
00:27:20.769 --> 00:27:22.770
I swear. I find the rat…

361
00:27:22.771 --> 00:27:24.397
Quit lookin’ at me. Byers.
or I’ll put your lights out.

362
00:27:24.398 --> 00:27:26.774
Any of time. girl.

363
00:27:26.775 --> 00:27:29.615
McDOWELL: Now. we’re forced
to divert. or the firm’s
legally on the hook.

364
00:27:31.572 --> 00:27:34.240
You’ll head up
this rescue. or salvage.

365
00:27:34.241 --> 00:27:35.867
whatever we’re calling it.

366
00:27:35.868 --> 00:27:36.988
Put a shuttle team together.

367
00:27:40.873 --> 00:27:42.707
Is there a problem. XO?

368
00:27:42.708 --> 00:27:44.793
Acting XO. sir.

369
00:27:50.966 --> 00:27:52.592
I ain’t goin’.
No way. no how.

370
00:27:52.593 --> 00:27:54.886
Well. you ain’t invited.

371
00:27:54.887 --> 00:27:56.971
Alex. ping the beacon
that we’re on our way

372
00:27:56.972 --> 00:27:58.472
and let Ceres know that
we’re gonna be late.

373
00:27:58.473 --> 00:28:00.349
Ms. Nygaard?

374
00:28:00.350 --> 00:28:01.642
If we flip right now
and burn like hell.

375
00:28:01.643 --> 00:28:04.187
I can get us within
50.000 clicks.

376
00:28:04.188 --> 00:28:06.314
Oh. great.
Then we’ll all be puking
in our crash-couches

377
00:28:06.315 --> 00:28:08.399
while the cargo busts loose
and scuttles the ship.

378
00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:10.526
Make sure that ice stays put.

379
00:28:10.527 --> 00:28:12.862
Naomi. How’s the
<i>Knight</i> looking?

380
00:28:12.863 --> 00:28:15.823
She’s one leaky lifeboat.

381
00:28:15.824 --> 00:28:17.867
She should be able
to manage 50.000
clicks of vacuum.

382
00:28:17.868 --> 00:28:19.148
All right. then you’re on board.

383
00:28:24.750 --> 00:28:27.043
This is Holden.

384
00:28:27.044 --> 00:28:32.173
We’ve logged a distress call
near CA-2216862.

385
00:28:32.174 --> 00:28:34.717
<i>We’re obliged to change
our course and respond.</i>

386
00:28:34.718 --> 00:28:37.762
<i>Make sure your acceleration
drug dispensers are full.</i>

387
00:28:37.763 --> 00:28:40.003
<i>This will be
a high-G maneuver.
Prepare for flip and burn.</i>

388
00:28:55.864 --> 00:28:56.864
Here comes the juice.

389
00:30:31.793 --> 00:30:34.962
I can’t figure out why Cap
would put you in charge
of this little excursion.

390
00:30:34.963 --> 00:30:36.130
Well. he still thinks
he’s grooming me

391
00:30:36.131 --> 00:30:38.049
for bigger things.

392
00:30:38.050 --> 00:30:40.384
Then he’s wasting his time.

393
00:30:40.385 --> 00:30:41.625
That’s what I keep telling him.

394
00:30:46.600 --> 00:30:48.360
If your girlfriend logged
that distress call.

395
00:30:49.936 --> 00:30:51.696
she’s gonna be
living it down
for a long time.

396
00:30:58.612 --> 00:30:59.696
I did it.

397
00:31:06.036 --> 00:31:07.037
I just couldn’t shake it.

398
00:31:10.499 --> 00:31:12.167
I’d keep that to myself
if I were you.

399
00:31:19.549 --> 00:31:20.759
What’s the good word. y’all?

400
00:31:21.885 --> 00:31:24.053
All right.

401
00:31:24.054 --> 00:31:27.181
How’s my sweet old
rust bucket today?

402
00:31:27.182 --> 00:31:29.100
Well. I guess we’ll
find out. won’t we?

403
00:31:29.101 --> 00:31:30.143
I guess so.

404
00:31:38.276 --> 00:31:40.569
So just for the record. guys.

405
00:31:40.570 --> 00:31:42.029
I don’t wanna be here right now.

406
00:31:42.030 --> 00:31:44.907
Me neither.
But here we are.

407
00:31:44.908 --> 00:31:47.201
One big. happy unit.

408
00:31:47.202 --> 00:31:49.161
Knight. <i>your flight plan is set.</i>

409
00:31:49.162 --> 00:31:51.664
<i>It’ll be a two-hour trip to
the tango. flying tea-kettle.</i>

410
00:31:51.665 --> 00:31:53.332
<i>Thank you.</i> Canterbury.

411
00:31:53.333 --> 00:31:57.002
<i>Welcome.</i> Knight.
<i>Godspeed.</i>

412
00:31:57.003 --> 00:31:58.963
If you see anything that
seems off. you pack up
the toys and come on home.

413
00:31:58.964 --> 00:32:01.173
No heroes. Captain.

414
00:32:01.174 --> 00:32:02.884
Clear to leave the barn.
Good luck.

415
00:32:32.873 --> 00:32:33.957
Really?

416
00:32:37.210 --> 00:32:39.753
She’s off the clock.

417
00:32:39.754 --> 00:32:40.964
Then she can tell me that.

418
00:32:54.269 --> 00:32:56.061
I’d keep an eye on that guy.

419
00:32:56.062 --> 00:33:00.399
I hear he collects
moon rocks in his
spare time.

420
00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:01.942
You wanna know
what else he’s into?

421
00:33:01.943 --> 00:33:04.863
Hey. hey. now. I’m just
lookin’ out for you.

422
00:33:07.282 --> 00:33:08.362
I need a woman’s intuition.

423
00:33:10.911 --> 00:33:12.286
Who is she?

424
00:33:12.287 --> 00:33:15.331
Oh. she’s just
a missing persons case

425
00:33:15.332 --> 00:33:16.932
I’m not “permitted
to discuss.” you know.

426
00:33:19.002 --> 00:33:21.921
Juliette Andromeda Mao.

427
00:33:21.922 --> 00:33:23.682
She’s the richest
bachelorette in the system.

428
00:33:25.258 --> 00:33:28.385
Now what would a rich girl do

429
00:33:28.386 --> 00:33:31.096
to really piss
Daddy off on Ceres?

430
00:33:31.097 --> 00:33:32.182
Are you asking what I did?

431
00:33:34.518 --> 00:33:35.958
Bang every space
bucker I could find.

432
00:33:37.604 --> 00:33:39.813
That’s not helpful.

433
00:33:39.814 --> 00:33:41.626
Oh. I’m sorry. Miller.
Did you come here
for my help?

434
00:33:41.650 --> 00:33:44.693
Come on.

435
00:33:44.694 --> 00:33:47.447
Admit it. You miss me.
You miss these little chats.

436
00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:50.075
Good night. Miller.

437
00:33:58.959 --> 00:34:00.879
Eat something.
for God’s sake.
You look like hell.

438
00:34:21.398 --> 00:34:23.441
<i>Config matches
the registry information.</i>

439
00:34:24.943 --> 00:34:27.361
It’s definitely the <i>Scopuli.</i>

440
00:34:27.362 --> 00:34:30.739
No IR or
electro-mag other than
the distress beacon.

441
00:34:30.740 --> 00:34:32.074
Looks like the
reactor’s shut down.

442
00:34:32.075 --> 00:34:33.702
but no radiation leakage.

443
00:34:36.204 --> 00:34:38.564
What about that thing
that looks like a big hole
in the side?

444
00:34:40.083 --> 00:34:42.836
Uh. LADAR says
it’s a big hole
in the side.

445
00:34:46.423 --> 00:34:50.175
Well. the big array
on the <i>Cant</i>’s reading no one
within a million clicks.

446
00:34:50.176 --> 00:34:52.094
Looks like we’re
the only game in town.

447
00:34:52.095 --> 00:34:53.615
Well. we came. we looked.
we. uh. left.

448
00:34:55.348 --> 00:34:57.228
No one’s gonna know
if we set foot
on that thing.

449
00:35:00.312 --> 00:35:03.022
Take us in.

450
00:35:03.023 --> 00:35:06.275
And. Alex.
if something nasty’s
hiding in that ship.

451
00:35:06.276 --> 00:35:07.985
we bolt like hell
and melt anything
behind us into slag.

452
00:35:07.986 --> 00:35:09.778
Good plan. Hoss.

453
00:35:09.779 --> 00:35:11.259
All right.
I’ll go in and poke around.

454
00:35:14.075 --> 00:35:15.201
I’ll go with him.

455
00:35:32.010 --> 00:35:33.053
Good times.

456
00:36:10.507 --> 00:36:11.747
How do you think that happened?

457
00:36:14.135 --> 00:36:16.179
It wasn’t a torpedo.
A breaching charge did that.

458
00:36:22.143 --> 00:36:24.937
Amos.

459
00:36:24.938 --> 00:36:25.938
Keep that gun out.

460
00:36:29.401 --> 00:36:31.682
Engineering first.
I wanna know why
that reactor’s offline.

461
00:36:48.211 --> 00:36:49.796
Reactor wasn’t
killed by the
blast.

462
00:36:52.132 --> 00:36:53.892
Someone went through
the shutdown procedures.

463
00:36:56.386 --> 00:36:57.986
So. if everyone’s
dead. who turned
it off?

464
00:36:59.514 --> 00:37:00.557
Well. it wasn’t pirates.

465
00:37:02.809 --> 00:37:05.269
They wouldn’t
have left all
that behind.

466
00:37:05.270 --> 00:37:06.870
And they left
all the pressure
doors open.

467
00:37:10.400 --> 00:37:11.735
So no one could hide.

468
00:37:17.157 --> 00:37:18.908
Six o’clock!

469
00:37:22.412 --> 00:37:23.997
Naomi. Shed.
we need more eyes in here.

470
00:37:27.125 --> 00:37:28.405
All right. Meet us
on the bridge.

471
00:37:45.226 --> 00:37:46.394
Hey. guys?

472
00:37:48.480 --> 00:37:51.440
Where are all the bodies at?

473
00:37:51.441 --> 00:37:54.486
Amos. cut out
the data core.
We’ll take it with us.

474
00:37:56.070 --> 00:37:57.197
Roger that.

475
00:38:01.910 --> 00:38:05.078
These panels are all dead.

476
00:38:05.079 --> 00:38:07.199
How are they sending
a distress beacon
with dead comms?

477
00:38:26.309 --> 00:38:27.601
Does that look like a…

478
00:38:27.602 --> 00:38:29.520
Well. maybe not…

479
00:38:29.521 --> 00:38:31.272
If it was a bomb. we’d be toast.

480
00:38:33.983 --> 00:38:34.983
It’s a transmitter.

481
00:38:40.281 --> 00:38:42.324
This must be
the beacon that called us.

482
00:38:42.325 --> 00:38:44.159
Somebody planted it.

483
00:38:44.160 --> 00:38:46.620
Pirate bait.

484
00:38:46.621 --> 00:38:49.748
McDowell was right.

485
00:38:49.749 --> 00:38:52.030
<i>Hoss. forwarding you
an A-1 tight-beam
from the</i> Canterbury.

486
00:38:53.837 --> 00:38:57.631
Holden. a ship
just appeared
near your location.

487
00:38:57.632 --> 00:38:59.992
<i>How is that possible?
You cleared us out
to a million clicks.</i>

488
00:39:01.261 --> 00:39:03.595
It didn’t show up on
any of our scopes.

489
00:39:03.596 --> 00:39:06.015
We’re setting you
a rendezvous point.
Get the hell back here.

490
00:39:17.318 --> 00:39:18.610
Alex! Disengage!

491
00:39:18.611 --> 00:39:19.696
My pleasure.

492
00:39:22.490 --> 00:39:24.659
Disengaging!

493
00:39:34.252 --> 00:39:35.961
Where did that thing come from?

494
00:39:35.962 --> 00:39:38.338
Damned if I know!
Just suddenly.
it was there.

495
00:39:38.339 --> 00:39:40.173
Stealth tech.
Has to be.

496
00:39:40.174 --> 00:39:41.534
Who the hell has
stealth like that?

497
00:39:43.011 --> 00:39:44.095
Mars.

498
00:40:02.530 --> 00:40:04.197
That’s more thinner
to the mix. all right?

499
00:40:04.198 --> 00:40:06.241
All right.

500
00:40:06.242 --> 00:40:08.410
Hey. hey.
you see that other one?

501
00:40:08.411 --> 00:40:11.538
- What was that?
- You got that
other one with you?

502
00:40:11.539 --> 00:40:14.416
That’s a cute kid.
How old?

503
00:40:14.417 --> 00:40:15.417
Two and a half.

504
00:40:19.589 --> 00:40:20.632
How about you?
Any kids?

505
00:40:22.675 --> 00:40:25.136
Yeah. no.
I missed that boat.

506
00:40:50.203 --> 00:40:51.287
There you go. pal.

507
00:40:54.707 --> 00:40:56.292
My turn.

508
00:40:57.585 --> 00:41:00.212
My turn.

509
00:41:00.213 --> 00:41:01.464
Me turn. me turn!

510
00:41:12.684 --> 00:41:15.143
We had an understanding.
Detective! An arrangement!

511
00:41:15.144 --> 00:41:16.504
You can’t just…
It was a mistake!

512
00:41:28.116 --> 00:41:30.659
You made your point.
I’m a changed man!

513
00:41:30.660 --> 00:41:32.620
Thank you for opening my eyes!

514
00:41:37.208 --> 00:41:38.208
Twice the money!

515
00:41:40.753 --> 00:41:41.753
I’ll pay you double!

516
00:41:50.263 --> 00:41:52.682
Air is good. don’t you think?

517
00:41:55.309 --> 00:41:56.394
Air is nice.

518
00:41:59.355 --> 00:42:00.675
Keep those filters
clean. asshole.

519
00:42:05.486 --> 00:42:06.486
<i>Knight.</i> we have your rendezvous.

520
00:42:06.487 --> 00:42:07.487
Negative. Unable.

521
00:42:07.488 --> 00:42:09.156
Advise.

522
00:42:09.157 --> 00:42:10.699
Bogey is 12.000 clicks
and closing.

523
00:42:10.700 --> 00:42:11.784
<i>Holden. advise!</i>

524
00:42:16.205 --> 00:42:18.248
Torpedo launch!

525
00:42:18.249 --> 00:42:20.000
We’re gonna take ’em
for a ride. Alex.
go around the asteroid.

526
00:42:20.001 --> 00:42:23.086
Run ’em! Now!
Lead the torpedoes
into the rock.

527
00:42:23.087 --> 00:42:24.567
<i>What is your situation?
Please advise!</i>

528
00:42:28.426 --> 00:42:30.553
Six thousand clicks.

529
00:42:46.277 --> 00:42:47.403
Those weren’t meant for us.

530
00:42:50.698 --> 00:42:52.578
<i>Canterbury.</i> burn like hell.
you’ve got incoming!

531
00:42:55.828 --> 00:42:57.580
Right 30. G-burn.
Do it! Now!

532
00:42:58.748 --> 00:43:00.957
Range?
Two-four. Closing.

533
00:43:00.958 --> 00:43:02.250
McDOWELL: Standby cargo door.

534
00:43:02.251 --> 00:43:03.835
Captain. eject the ice
as a shield.

535
00:43:03.836 --> 00:43:05.087
We’re on it!
Stay off this channel.

536
00:43:05.088 --> 00:43:06.963
Ade?

537
00:43:06.964 --> 00:43:08.548
<i>Ade. did Mac eject the ice?</i>

538
00:43:08.549 --> 00:43:11.426
Did he eject the ice?

539
00:43:11.427 --> 00:43:14.554
You take a hit. you stay calm.
They just want the cargo.

540
00:43:14.555 --> 00:43:15.680
We’ll SOS. start negotiations
for prisoner release. okay?

541
00:43:15.681 --> 00:43:17.599
Just…
<i>Jim.</i>

542
00:43:17.600 --> 00:43:19.310
<i>There’s something
you should know…</i>

543
00:43:51.425 --> 00:43:52.552
She’s gone.

544
00:44:04.480 --> 00:44:05.565
They nuked her.

545
00:44:08.526 --> 00:44:09.610
She’s gone.

546
00:44:10.305 --> 00:45:10.945
